Convert xml-protected spaces to real spaces

Because they can disturb later processing. See #9.

Remove <text:soft-page-break>

We don't need it for our output and it may disturb the processing of
headlines later. Closes #9.

And fixed whitespace, while at it. Closes #8.

Properly compare mem_num_malloced == mem_num_freed

Of course we want to compare the number of mallocs with the number of freed memory, and not the number of mallocs with itself ;-)

Make libzip the default zip library

And discourage use of kunzip. See issue #7

Sanity checks for broken length records in zipfiles

This regards kunzip only. libzip has a much better handling of broken
files. libzip should have been become default a long time ago.

Fixes #7

Fix warning about signed/unsigned comparison

With HAVE_LIBZIP=1 and -Wsign-compare

Resync license file with FSF version

Downloaded from https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-2.0.txt

Resolves #5

Since I first added the license file a few years ago, the FSF has
published a slightly updated version. Fedora seems to see the
differences between the old version and the now-official version as a
bug.

The only two differences between both versions are
  * new FSF address
  * LGPL is now addressed as GNU _Lesser_ PL
